BY PRIMROSE HAISA JOICE Matanhire (42) from Mutoko is appealing for help to get treatment for her brother Austine Matinhire (49), who developed a growth in the mouth following a tooth extraction in 1995. Matanhire said doctors have recommended that her brother must undergo surgery as part of cancer treatment, but the family was struggling to raise the US$1 500 demanded for the procedure at Parirenyatwa Group of Hospitals. The family has only managed to raise US$300 which has already gone towards funding the screening process. Matanhire can be contacted on 0776 684 569. l Follow Primrose on Twitter
